{{nihongo|'''Tomoki Hayakawa'''|早川 友基|Hayakawa Tomoki|born 3 March 1999}} is a Japanese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Japanese football updater|KashimaA}} club [[Kashima Antlers]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=早川 友基：鹿島アントラーズ：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/player/1632225/#gk |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=20 December 2022 |language=ja}}</ref>

==Club career==
Hayakawa made his professional debut in a 8–1 [[Emperor's Cup]] win against [[YSCC Yokohama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jfa.jp/match/emperorscup_2021/match_page/m39.html|title=鹿島アントラーズ 8–1 Ｙ.Ｓ.Ｃ.Ｃ.横浜|date=16 June 2021|accessdate=16 June 2021|website=jfa.jp|language=Japanese}}</ref> He made his J1 League debut in the 2022 season, in a 1–1 draw with [[Sagan Tosu]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Soccer D.B. : 2022 J1 League 22/09/16 Sagan Tosu - Kashima Antlers Results,Players,Highlight |url=https://soccer-db.net/result.php?g=20220916001&la=e |website=Soccer D.B. |access-date=20 December 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

In the 2023 season, Hayakawa became first-choice goalkeeper for Kashima and played in every league game. Before the 2024 season, he was given the number 1 shirt following the retirement of [[Kwoun Sun-tae]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2024シーズントップチーム登録選手のお知らせ {{!}} 鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト |url=https://www.antlers.co.jp/news/team_info/97712 |website=鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト {{!}} KASHIMA ANTLERS |access-date=9 January 2024 |language=ja}}</ref> In the 2024 season, Hayakawa also participated in every league game for the club and kept 15 clean sheets, the second most in the league.<ref>{{cite web |title=MEIJI YASUDA J1 LEAGUE {{!}} 2024 Stats |url=https://jleague.co/stats/dashboard/j1/2024/ |website=J.LEAGUE |access-date=15 January 2025 |language=en}}</ref>

In 2025, he played every minute of every league match for the third consecutive season and was named the Save of the Month award winner four times, contributing to Kashima's ninth league championship and their first in nine years. He was awarded the J.League Most Valuable Player award for the 2025 season at the J.League Awards ceremony held on 11 December.<ref name="2025-player-of-the-year" />

== International career ==
Hayakawa was called up [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]] squad for the [[2025 EAFF E-1 Football Championship]]. He made his debut on 12 July 2025 in a 2–0 win over [[China national football team|China]].

On 15 May 2026, Hayakawa was named in Japan's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー・スケジュール キリンチャレンジカップ2026 ひとつになるから強くなる。 5.31 アイスランド代表戦（5.31 東京／国立競技場）FIFAワールドカップ2026（6.11-7.19 カナダ・メキシコ・アメリカ） |url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00036338/ |website=www.jfa.jp |access-date=15 May 2026 |language=ja}}</ref>

